<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-766-431  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 766 431.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The New York Times  July 19 1989 v138 n47,936 pA1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>In shift, U.S. eases computer exports to Eastern bloc: a step toexpand trade; industry hails the move, but some former Pentagonofficials are critical.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gordon, Michael R.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Commerce Department announces a shift in the American exportpolicy that will allow sale of a wide range of microcomputers tothe Soviet Union and Eastern-bloc countries.andP;  The announcementcomes just after Pres Bush returned from an Eastern European tripthat included stops in Poland and Hungary.andP;  The CommerceDepartment says the action was justified as microcomputers similarto those banned by the US have been sold to the Eastern bloc fromother countries including Singapore, Taiwan, India and Brazil.andO;Some former Pentagon officials have sharply criticized the move.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Department of CommerceMicrocomputersExportSoviet UnionTechnology TransferInternational Trade.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>